            .</p>
               <p>JAMES MACKENZIE. I am a <rs id="t18280529-244-viclabel1343" type="occupation">ladies' shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-244-victim1322 t18280529-244-viclabel1343"></join>. I<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182805290104"></xptr>came to town on Tuesday, and left my box on board the smack at <placeName id="t18280529-244-crimeloc1344">Hoares' wharf</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-244-crimeloc1344" type="placeName" value="Hoares' wharf"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-244-crimeloc1344" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-244-off1341 t18280529-244-crimeloc1344"></join>, in care of the steward; when I returned on Thursday, one box, containing these articles was gone; some persons on board gave me information - Crighton took us to a house in Rosemary-lane, where the prisoner lived; the people were out - I went for a constable, he came and found the box in the back room; it had been broken open, and several things taken out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-244-person1323">
                  DAVID 
                  CRIGHTON
               <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1323" type="surname" value="CRIGHTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1323" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter, and work at Hoares' wharf. I carried a yellow trunk by the prisoner's order, from the vessel to the White Swan public-house, Rosemary-lane; he went there with me - he said it was his own - I was on the wharf waiting for a job; I am sure he said it was his own, and he said he was a passenger in that vessel, the Forfairshire; I was called again at eight o'clock that night, and went with the prosecutor to find it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-244-person1324">
                  JOSEPH 
                  KING
               <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1324" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1324" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1324" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter. The prisoner applied to me on Thursday afternoon last, to carry a box from the White Swan; I took it to a house in Brown's-buildings, Princes street, and left it there - he said it was his box. I afterwards went with the prosecutor, who claimed the same box - there was a rope round it, and it appeared locked.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-244-person1325">
                  SARAH 
                  HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1325" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1325" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1325" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Brown's-buildings; the prisoner was a friend of my husband's; he called on Thursday, and asked me to let him leave this box in my place, which I did; the prosecutor came and took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-244-person1326">
                  JOHN 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1326" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1326" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1326" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I found the box in Brown's-buildings, with some articles in it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-244-person1327">
                  CHARLES 
                  WALLER
               <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1327" type="surname" value="WALLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1327" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-person1327" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner in Rosemary-lane, and found a shirt, trousers, coat, and waistcoat, on him - he was dressed in them, and his own coat was left in the box, which had been broken open with a chisel or hatchet.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I expected a box from Scotland; I had been drinking rather freely, and thought this was mine - the linen is marked as my own.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280529-244-verdict1345" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-244-verdict1345" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 52.</p>
